'''Ahmad''' is a [[Impact crater|crater]] in the northern hemisphere of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Ahmad was first discovered in ''[[Voyager 2]]'' images but was seen at much higher resolution, though near the [[Terminator (solar)|terminator]], by ''[[Cassini-Huygens Mission|Cassini]]''.  It is located at 58.8° North [[Latitude]], 311.6° West [[Longitude]] and is 18.7 kilometers across.<ref name="USGS"/>  The western portion of the crater is largely absent, either buried or disrupted by the eastern margin of [[Samarkand Sulci]].  A large, dome-like structure occupies the interior of the crater, caused by infill of material from Samarkand Sulci or from viscous relaxation.

[[Ahmed (Arabian Nights)|Ahmad]] is named after a hero from ''[[Arabian Nights]]''.  He brings his father an apple and marries [[Peri-Banu]].

