'''Gerhard Haszprunar''' (born 25 February 1957 in Vienna) is Austrian [[zoologist]] and [[malacologist]].<ref name="zsm.mwn.de">[http://www.zsm.mwn.de/dir/e/curriculum.htm Curriculum vitae: Prof. Dr. Gerhard Haszprunar] Accessed 3 December 2010.</ref>
He is credited with the invention of the modern species naming patrongage model<ref name="fundingecologicalresearch">{{cite web|accessdate=June 18, 2011|url=http://www.unep.org/dec/onlinemanual/Enforcement/InstitutionalFrameworks/EconomicInstruments/Resource/tabid/1014/Default.aspx|title=Financing conservation efforts by selling naming rights of new species}}</ref> and is a founder of the [[BIOPAT_-_Patrons_for_Biodiversity|BIOPAT]] non-profit organization.
==Honours and awards== * Cardinal Innitzer prize (for the Habilitation) (1989) * Prize of the city of Innsbruck for scientific research at the [[University of Innsbruck]] for the project "Monoplacophora" (with Dr. [[Kurt Schaefer]]) (1994) * [[Austrian Decoration for Science and Art|Austrian Cross of Honour for Science and Art]] (2008)<ref name="zsm.mwn.de"/> <ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.parlament.gv.at/PAKT/VHG/XXIV/AB/AB_10542/imfname_251156.pdf | title = Reply to a parliamentary question | language = German | page=1841 |trans-title=| format = pdf | accessdate = 16 November 2012 }}</ref>
