{{Taxobox | image = | image_caption = | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Planctomycetes]] | classis = [[Planctomycetacia]] | subclassis = | ordo = [[Planctomycetales]] | subordo = | familia = [[Isosphaeraceae]] | genus = '''''Paludisphaera''''' | genus_authority = Kulichevskaya et al. 2016<ref name=Paludisphaera>{{cite journal |last1=Parte |first1=A.C. |title=Paludisphaera |journal=www.bacterio.net |url=http://www.bacterio.net/paludisphaera.html}}</ref> | type_species = ''Paludisphaera borealis''<ref name=Paludisphaera/> | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = ''[[Paludisphaera borealis|P. borealis]]''<ref name=Paludisphaera/> | synonyms = }}
'''''Paludisphaera''''' is an [[Aerobic organism|aerobic]] genus of bacteria from the family of [[Isosphaeraceae]] with one known species (''[[Paludisphaera borealis]]'').<ref name=Paludisphaera/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Paludisphaera |journal=www.uniprot.org |url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1763521 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Parker |first1=Charles Thomas |last2=Garrity |first2=George M |title=Taxonomic Abstract for the genera. |journal=The NamesforLife Abstracts |date=1 January 2003 |doi=10.1601/tx.28229 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=PMID>{{cite journal |last1=Kulichevskaya |first1=IS |last2=Ivanova |first2=AA |last3=Suzina |first3=NE |last4=Rijpstra |first4=WIC |last5=Sinninghe Damsté |first5=JS |last6=Dedysh |first6=SN |title=''Paludisphaera borealis'' gen. nov., sp. nov., a hydrolytic planctomycete from northern wetlands, and proposal of ''Isosphaeraceae'' fam. nov. |journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology |date=February 2016 |volume=66 |issue=2 |pages=837–844 |doi=10.1099/ijsem.0.000799 |pmid=26611145}}</ref> ''Paludisphaera borealis''has been isolated from [[Sphagnum]] peat from the [[Yaroslavl region]] in [[Russia]].<ref name=PMID/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Details: DSM-28747 |journal=www.dsmz.de |url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-28747.html |language=en}}</ref>
